<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kekilbayev Shows Interest in Indian Self-Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kekilbayev Shows Interest in Indian Self-Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606130794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1118 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Kulagin] </F>
  [Text] Almaty 6 June TASS -- During his meeting with 
visiting Indian Minister of State for External Affairs Salman 
Khurshid, who arrived in Almaty on Sunday [5 June], Speaker of 
Kazakhstan's Parliament Abish Kekilbayev displayed special 
interest in India's experience of resolving problems of local 
self-government. The two leaders also discussed questions of 
ecology, flood-prevention measures, and other topical problems. 
  The two sides expressed the hope that their bilateral ties 
would progressively broaden on the international, as well as 
interparliamentary levels. Abish Kekilbayev handed over an 
invitation to the Indian parliamentary delegation to visit 
Kazakhstan in the second half of 1994. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

