<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indian Foreign Minister Comments on Nazarbayev Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Indian Foreign Minister Comments on Nazarbayev Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606143894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1351 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by KAZTAG correspondent Ivan Zakharchenko for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Almaty 6 June TASS -- "India fully supports Kazakh 
President Nursultan Nazarbayev's initiative to convene a 
conference on measures to promote trust and cooperation in Asia, 
and he is actively participating in its realisation," State 
Indian Foreign Minister Salman Khurshid said on Monday [6 June]. 
  The minister made this statement after his delegation was 
received by the Kazakh president. Touched upon the Kashmir 
problem the Indian diplomat noted that the Kazakh president "is 
doing everything possible for its fair and peaceful settlement." 
  The two sides discussed the implementation of agreements on 
developing trade and economic ties between the two countries. 
Indian businessmen arrived in Almaty to establish contacts with 
Kazakh entrepreneurs, the Indian foreign minister stressed. 
  During Khurshid's meeting with the president, they also 
discussed the pace of work on the agreement on mutual 
investments to provide firm guarantees and the activity of the 
Council of Business Cooperation with Kazakhstan created by 
India, which includes directors of private enterprises. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

