<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kazakhstanis Disillusioned With National Currency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kazakhstanis Disillusioned With National Currency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0606154594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 4 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0606154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "Most Polled Kazakhstanis Want Return to </F>
Ruble Zone"] 
  [Text] Many Kazakhstanis think it was a mistake to bring 
in their own currency last November. 
  This is shown by an opinion poll taken in the Republic by 
Alma-Ata's [Almaty's] Giller Institute. Some 62.5 percent of 
those residents of the capital who were polled are convinced 
that the country should return to the ruble zone. Only 21 
percent of respondents categorically oppose this step. In the 
six months the national currency has been in existence, its 
value has fallen more than eight times over. 

</TEXT>

