<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Russian-Tajik Forces Patrol Dushanbe Streets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Russian-Tajik Forces Patrol Dushanbe Streets </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606131994 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 1200 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tajik </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] For the third successive day, servicemen of the 
Defense Ministry of Tajikistan and representatives of the 
Russian Army in Tajikistan and of the Internal Affairs Ministry 
are manning checkpoints in Dushanbe. Their joint action stems 
from the fact that in recent days the sociopolitical situation 
in Dushanbe has deteriorated slightly. Several military 
servicemen have fallen victim to bullets fired by criminal 
elements. This is why joint security groups are observing the 
sociopolitical situation in the city at the orders of the 
republican leadership and also observing the agreement of the 
military leaders of the Russian Federation in Tajikistan. 
  According to the press office of the Internal Affairs 
Ministry, criminal incidents have decreased compared to several 
days ago as a result of joint efforts by the joint security 
bodies. 

</TEXT>

