<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karimov Plans Joining NATO Partnership for Peace Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karimov Plans Joining NATO Partnership for Peace Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606114594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1100 GMT 
6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Uzbekistan intends to join NATO's Partnership for 
Peace program. This was announced at a news conference in 
Tashkent today by the Republic's president, Islam Karimov. In 
his words, membership in the program is aimed at protecting 
Uzbekistan's own interests. At the same time Karimov pointed 
out that Russia remains the main guarantor of stability in 
Central Asia. 

</TEXT>

