<H3> <TI>   Azeris Reportedly Shell Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azeris Reportedly Shell Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606152794 Yerevan SNARK in English 0807 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0606152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, June 6 (SNARK)--The relative peace in 
Karabakh, lasting for three weeks already, was violated last 
night by shellings of the positions of Karabakh Defence Army 
forces at the south-east (Martuninskiy) sector of the front. 
The Azerbaijani side used grenade launchers and various types 
of automatic weapons. As SNARK was informed in the Karabakh 
State Department of Information and Press, there had been no 
retaliate fire from the Karabakh side. No reports on the 
consequences. 
  Despite such actions, the observers tend to think that the 
truce is kept, on the whole. 

</TEXT>

