<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Trade Agreement Signed With Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0606132594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 4 Jun 94 
First Edition p 6 </F>

<F P=103> PM0606132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Karen Topchyan report: "Armenia-Iran: Ties Broaden"] </F>
  [Text] Armenia and Iran have signed an agreement on border 
trade between Armenia's Megrinskiy Rayon and Iran's Marand 
Province. This document envisages opening in the next few days 
a permanent market on the Armenian-Iranian border which will 
sell mainly clothing and foodstuffs duty-free. 
  This agreement is by no means the first joint document. 
Today over a dozen treaties are being implemented between the 
two neighboring countries in the sphere of politics, the 
economy, culture, and sport. Iran is Armenia's second most 
important economic partner after Russia. 

</TEXT>

