<H3> <TI>   Russian Nuclear Energy Specialists on `Working Visit' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Nuclear Energy Specialists on `Working Visit' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0506201394 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0646 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0506201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan ("AZG" daily), 06/04/94 -- As we have 
already reported, a delegation of the Russian Ministry of Energy 
visited Armenia. The delegation involves some twenty 
specialists in nuclear energy. 
  An "Azg" correspondent met the director of "Energia" 
enterprise, Director of the Russian institute of Nuclear Plants 
Use, Doctor of Technical Sciences, Prof. Armen Abaghian. 
  - Mr. Abaghian, why did you arrive to Yerevan? 
  - This is a working visit. You probably know that Russian 
Federation and Armenia signed an agreement on reopening the 
Armenian Nuclear Power Plant, and the majority of work will be 
carried by our specialists. We arrived to get acquainted with 
current state of the power plant and to define basic directions 
of our activity. 
  - What are the conditions at the plant? 
  - After preliminary operations, the plant is ready to 
reconstruction. 
  - There have been rumors that most of the equipment is 
stolen, is this true? 
  - This are senseless rumors. It's not easy to steal things 
from here. All main elements are in normal conditions. 
  - What's the main problem today? 
  - Financing. Some 100 million dollars are needed for 
reopening the block. Everything else is clear. 
  - Do you have security specialists in your delegation? 
  - Sure, the problems of physical security have been 
discussed in detail. These are all soluble problems and one 
shouldn't dramatize these. 
  - If the problem of financing is solved, do you think that 
the plant may be started up by winter. 
  - Yes, this is possible. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

