<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Georgia Insists on Joint Command of Russian Bases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Georgia Insists on Joint Command of Russian Bases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606200994 Yerevan SNARK in English 1513 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0606200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, June 6 (SNARK)--Rezo Adamia, secretary of 
the Georgian Parliament Commission on Defence and National 
Security told SNARK today Georgia insists on joint command over 
Russian military bases, stationed in Georgia. In his opinion, 
the command over the Russian bases should be implemented on 
coordination with Commander- in-Chief of Georgian Army. 
  Besides, we suggest that in the Russian troops, should also 
serve Georgians, but the Russian side is very suspicious in this 
question. Among the serious discords at the negotiations is also 
the problem of the terms of the troops' staying. Russia insists 
on the term of 25 years, but Rezo Adamia considers that the 
agreement should be signed for 5 years. It will allow to revise 
it and to move necessary amendments every 5 years. "We should 
follow the example of the American bases in Philippines," said 
the MP. 

</TEXT>

