<DOCNO> FBIS4-39207 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov109_s_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-109 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  6 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peacekeepers' Deployment `Unresolved' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peacekeepers' Deployment `Unresolved' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606171994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1521 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Geneva talks on the settlement of the conflict 
between Georgia and Abkhazia have been re-scheduled from June 9 
to 15 because the problem of the deployment of peace-keepers 
into the zone of the Georgian-Abkhazian conflict remains 
unresolved. 
  The press-service for the Abkhazian Ambassador in Moscow 
said 
the postponement was caused by the refusal of the Russian 
Federation Council to agree to the deployment of the 
peace-keeping force along the confrontation line along the 
Inguri River from June 10 to 15. 
  The Federation Council, which considered the problem last 
week, decided the reasons in favor of Russian troop deployment 
in the Georgian-Abkhazian conflict zone as outlined in the 
letter to the upper house of the Federal Assembly by President 
Yeltsin were insufficient. Members of the Federation Council 
also pointed to the absence of a legal basis to determining the 
status of the Russian troops outside the country. 
  Meanwhile, following the decision of the Federation Council, 
the Georgian leader Eduard Shevardnadze said in Tbilisi that 
Russian president Yeltsin had assured him in a telephone 
conversation of the early deployment of Russian peace-keepers 
into conflict zone. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-39208 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov109_s_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-109 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

