<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Vitaliy Denisov report: "Will Bandits Now Have </F>
Difficulties in Georgia?"] 
  [Text] Tbilisi -- A special-purpose paratroop brigade has 
appeared within Georgia's State Security Service. According to 
the service's chairman, Igor Giorgadze, brigade personnel have 
been trained at Russian special services training centers. The 
"special-purpose forces" include motorized rifle and combat 
engineer subunits and an antiterrorist squad. The "special 
forces" will cost the taxpayer around 5 billion Russian rubles a 
year. But, according to independent experts, the brigade will be 
capable of more than covering the expenditure on its upkeep. 
Provided of course that certain conditions are created for it 
to fight crime. 

</TEXT>

