<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crime Figures Released </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crime Figures Released </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0606173394 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1811 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0606173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 4/6/1994 -- Of some 16,202 
offences which have been registered in the five months of 1994, 
20 percent were serious crimes, stated today on the Moldovan 
radio Victor Catana, prime vice minister of interior. The 
number of crimes against individuals decreased; murders and 
attempted murder fell by 3.2 percent in comparison with 1993. 
According to him, the police has solved 41.1 percent of the 
total number of crimes; 64.1 percent of all offences inflicting 
serious injuries and 65.9 percent of rapes and attempted rape 
cases were solved. Catana specified that 27 percent of the 
offences were committed by workers, 5 percent by peasants and 68 
percent by other social categories. He expressed concern about 
the amount of crimes committed by jobless people and youngsters 
who do not study. The number of crimes committed by drunk 
people increased by 40.8 percent, people with penal records by 
39.7 percent, groups by 19.2 percent, minors by 36.3 percent 
and people who do not work or study by 27.7 percent, said Victor 
Catana. 

</TEXT>

