<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Russian-Chechen Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Russian-Chechen Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Leadership May Ask for Extradition </H4>

<F P=102> LD0606192494 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1800 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Chechen leadership may ask Russia to extradite 
Ruslan Khasbulatov and three opposition leaders: Doku Zavgayev, 
Chechen-Ingushetia's last Communist Party leader; Yaragi 
Mamodayev, head of the so-called government of popular trust, as 
well as Abdulla Bugayev, leader of Freedom political movement, 
and Salambek (Gadzhiyev), who are the most active opposition 
leaders. Official Groznyy accuses them of collusion with Russia 
and actions against the Chechen people. Also today, the Chechen 
Foreign Ministry called upon all foreign states to refrain from 
any contacts with the opposition. 

</TEXT>

