<H3> <TI>   Agrarian Party on `Accord for Russia' Movement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agrarian Party on `Accord for Russia' Movement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606111694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1022 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "The goals of the Accord for Russia movement -- the 
arrival to power of the opposition forces, the restoration of 
the Soviet Union, and economic and social order -- are 
compatible with the goals of the Agrarian Party, although our 
attitude to this movement is cautious, Chairman of the Agrarian 
Party Mikhail Lapshin told Interfax. He explained his position 
by the fact that the agrarians favored a broader coalition of 
opposition forces and by the fears lest agricultural workers 
might be used by one of this movement's wings to advance their 
own political interests. 
  The opposition forces cannot disregard the growing strength 
of the agrarian movement, he continued. The time has come when 
the left-wing forces must give their backing to agricultural 
workers, who are ready to act resolutely in accordance with the 
Constitution against the current regime, he said. 
  Lapshin signed the statement by the Accord for Russia 
movement's leaders, but did not attend the first session of its 
national council on May 28, saying that he was busy working in 
the State Duma. 

</TEXT>

