<H3> <TI>   Draft Law on State Budget To Be Adopted in Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Draft Law on State Budget To Be Adopted in Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606160794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1312 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The draft law on Russia's 1994 budget will 
definitely be adopted in June, State Duma Speaker Ivan Rybkin 
told Interfax on Monday. As we reported earlier, the discussion 
of the draft budget had been scheduled for June 8. 
  To quote Rybkin, allocations will be increased by a total of 
8 trillion rubles on research, military-conversion projects, 
science, education, culture and social welfare. 
  Jointly with the government, the State Duma is looking for 
additional sources of revenues, including arms exports. 
  Commenting on the Federation Council's recommendations to 
increase military spending from 37 trillion to 55 trillion 
rubles, Rybkin said: "Dreaming is no sin." 
  Asked about the reason behind his meeting with Yeltsin 
scheduled for Tuesday, he said that it would be a routine 
meeting held monthly on the first Tuesday to discuss the most 
urgent issues. 

</TEXT>

