<H3> <TI>   Novosibirsk Oblast Adopts Economic Stabilization Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Novosibirsk Oblast Adopts Economic Stabilization Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0706104394 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 7 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM0706104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Andrey Illarionov report: "Yet Another Plan"] </F>
  [Text] Novosibirsk -- The Novosibirsk Oblast 
Administration has drawn up a plan to stabilize the territory's 
economic position. 
  An extensive list of measures has been conceived aimed at 
seeking funding to resolve priority tasks in the oblast and to 
elaborate mechanisms for state regulation of the economy. 
  The plan's priorities include the development of 
agricultural 
production and support for the fuel and energy complex. The 
social section of the plan is aimed at preventing mass 
unemployment and a decline in living standards. 
  Scientists and specialists in Novosibirsk and the oblast's 
rayons will have to resolve such difficult tasks as organizing 
transactions between enterprises and ensuring economic 
regulation of food prices. 
  A science support fund is to be set up. 

</TEXT>

