<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester Calls Crimean Crisis `Internal Affair' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dniester Calls Crimean Crisis `Internal Affair' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0606171694 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1811 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0606171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 4/6/1994 -- "The leadership of 
the Dniester Republic considers the crisis in Crimea an internal 
affair of the Ukraine," declared to BASA Valeriy Litskay, state 
secretary of the self-proclaimed Dniester Republic. He 
mentioned that the Tiraspol officials are keeping in touch with 
Crimean leaders, but, in his opinion, these contacts are a 
matter of routine. According to the state secretary, the 
Simferopol authorities, despite rumours, have not asked for 
support from Tiraspol. Referring to the notion of creating a 
union of unrecognized states, suggested by the leaders of 
Nagorno-Karabakh, Valeriy Litskay stressed that the Tiraspol 
officials had not been officially requested to enter this union. 
"We had not been offered documents such as the statute or the 
program of the union. Our position concerning the Union of 
Unrecognized States will depend solely on the contents of such 
documents," mentioned Litskay. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

