<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet Officers Run for Mayor of Sevastopol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Black Sea Fleet Officers Run for Mayor of Sevastopol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0606140994 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 4 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0606140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Vladimir Pasyakin: "Who Will Become Chairman of </F>
the Sevastopol City Council?"] 
  [Text] Eleven candidates have registered in Sevastopol for 
the post of chairman of the City Council. They include Reserve 
Admiral Aleksey Kalinin, former commander of the Black Sea 
Fleet, Colonel Ivan Yermakov, former mayor of Sevastopol, 
Colonel Aleksey Melnikov, deputy head of Black Sea Fleet Air 
Force communications, and Rear Admiral Aleksandr Penkin, aide to 
the commander of the Black Sea Fleet for work with personnel. 
  This plethora of military candidates speaks for itself. 
Sevastopol is the Black Sea Fleet's main base. It is quite 
possible that a Black Sea Fleet serviceman will become head of 
the City Council. 

</TEXT>

