<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Council To Control Radio, Television </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Council To Control Radio, Television </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606191394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1717 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606191394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A National Council for Television and Radio has been 
set up in Ukraine in accordance with a decree by Ukrainian 
President Leonid Kravchuk. 
  The presidential and government press office told 
INTERFAX-Ukraine that the council had the right to suspend the 
activities of television and radio broadcasting stations which 
violate Ukraine's legislation and annul their broadcasting 
licences. 
  The council will be subordinate directly to the Ukrainian 
Supreme Soviet. 
  Among other functions entrusted to the council, there are 
granting licences for using broadcasting channels and control 
over the use of the private band. 
  According to the decree, the council will pursue state 
policy 
in the field of television and radio broadcasting regardless of 
the stations' form of property and supervise the implementation 
of the law on mass media. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

