<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says DPRK Will Be Nuclear-Free State </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says DPRK Will Be Nuclear-Free State </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606203194 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1930 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev [no dateline as received] DPRK Foreign Minister 
Kim Yong-nam, currently in Ukraine on an official visit, met 
Ukraine Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko 6 June. The talks can 
be seen as introductory and consultative in nature. A wide 
range of issues were discussed in their talks. The key issue 
was focused on the development of bilateral relations, the 
possibility of economic cooperation, and the establishment of a 
legal and contractual basis for that. It was noted that Ukraine 
and the DPRK had signed only two agreements to date. 
  In addition, the two officials voiced their countries' 
positions on nuclear issues. Kim Yong-nam declared that the 
DPRK intended firmly to become a nuclear-free state. The DPRK's 
position on the matter coincides with Ukraine's, he stressed. 
  The sides plan to sign a number of bilateral agreements at 
the end of the visit 9 June. 

</TEXT>

