<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says No `Pressure' Will Solve Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says No `Pressure' Will Solve Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606214194 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2100 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kiev, 8 Jun -- [passage omitted] DPRK Foreign 
Minister Kim Yong-nam is in Kiev on an official visit. He told 
reporters at Borispol airport that "No sanctions, no pressure 
put on us will help a fair and unbiased solution to our nuclear 
problems. We are against nuclear arms. If the United States 
sincerely intends to solve the so-called nuclear problem, they 
should get down to the third round of Korean-American 
negotiations." 
  "We welcome Ukraine's intention to become a nuclear-free 
state because we, too, are making every effort to make the 
Korean peninsula nuclear-free." 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

