<H3> <TI>   Donuzlava Officers Send Open Letter to Russian Navy Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Donuzlava Officers Send Open Letter to Russian Navy Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK0406120094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 4 Jun 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK0406120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "NEGA Reports" rubric: </F>
"Crimea"] 
  [Text] The officers and warrant officers of the naval base 
at Donuzlava have sent an open letter to Admiral Feliks Gromov, 
commander of the Russian Navy. It says in part: "The hopes 
placed on the delegations of Russia and Ukraine on the question 
of the Black Sea Fleet division have not come true. The news of 
the supposed transfer of the Crimean naval base to Ukraine 
causes a well-founded anxiety and an uncertainty for the future. 
Should the Donuzlava base be turned over to the Ukrainian Navy, 
the naval base along with the settlement would fall into decay. 
The daily life of most people in the Donuzlava garrison is 
connected with work in military units. None of us can even 
admit the thought that the Crimean naval base will be turned 
over to Ukraine. Should this happen, the more than 7,000 
officers and warrant officers and members of their families 
would be left without subsistence. Comrade Admiral, we have 
faith in you, and in the common sense of the politicians who are 
not going to allow the transfer of the Crimean naval base to the 
Ukrainian Navy." 

</TEXT>

