<H4>    Holds Talks in Khabarovsk </H4>

<F P=102> LD0706030894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2353 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706030894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Khabarovsk, 7 Jun--Today, on his way back to his 
motherland, Republic of Korea President Kim Yong-sam made a 
short stop in Khabarovsk. An honor guard was formed at the 
airport. At the steps to the "Boeing 747", the high-ranking 
guest was met by Viktor Ishayev, head of the Khabarovsk Kray 
administration, and other officials. A half-hour conversation 
took place between the kray's governor and the president of 
South Korea. Viktor Ishayev reported that an exchange of 
opinions had taken place on a number of problems relating to 
mutual relations between the Republic of Korea and the Far 
Eastern region. In particular, the issue of setting up a free 
economic zone and ways of further activating economic 
cooperation were examined. More than 30 joint Russian-Korean 
enterprises are currently operating in the kray, the leading 
South Korean firms "Samsung", "Goldstar", and others are 
represented. The president of South Korea guaranteed assistance 
in implementing a large-scale project to produce buses in the 
Amur region with the participation of the Korean side. 
  After an hour-long stay in Khabarovsk, the president of 
South 
Korea left by air for Vladivostok. 

</TEXT>

