<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on ROK President's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on ROK President's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Visits Vladivostok </H4>

<F P=102> LD0706061894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0425 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706061894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Vladivostok, 7 Jun--Completing an official visit to 
Russia, Republic of Korea President Kim Yong-sam arrived in 
Vladivostok today in transit. 
  Yevgeniy Nazdratenko, head of the Maritime Territory 
administration, held a ceremonial reception on the occasion. "Of 
all the regions of Russia, the Far East has one very important 
advantage: Geographically, it is part of the Asian Pacific 
region," the governor stressed in his speech at the ceremonial 
reception. "The enormous natural wealth of the territory, 
combined with the lengthy experience of development in market 
economy conditions accumulated by South Korea, create a 
favorable medium for the implementation of mutually beneficial 
projects." 
  In a reply speech, the Korean president noted that, "on the 
threshold of `the Pacific era', the Maritime Territory is 
becoming a genuine center of Korean-Russian cooperation. 
Effective joint activity is already under way--first and 
foremost in the field of fishing. Cooperation is being 
developed in other spheres as well. In particular, the Nakhodka 
industrial and technical park is being set up for Korean 
enterprises. A sea route linking Pusan and the Maritime 
Territory has been opened. Regular flights will start between 
Vladivostok and Seoul this year." 
  "Thus," Kim Yong-sam also noted, "it will be possible to fly 
from the Republic of Korea to Russia in just two hours, and this 
means that we will become closer neighbors." 
  In the afternoon, the president of South Korea and the 
officials accompanying him will visit the headquarters and one 
of the ships of the Pacific Fleet. 

</TEXT>

