<H3> <TI>   PRC Air Force Delegation Shows Interest in MIG-29 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Air Force Delegation Shows Interest in MIG-29 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606170894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1312 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606170894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commander of the Chinese Air Force Cao Shuangming, 
who arrived in Russia for an official visit, flew out to Sochi 
on Monday for a two-day stay in the military sanatorium of 
Chemitokvadzhe, located in the village of Lazarevskoye. 
  According to military sources, the Chinese delegation,led by 
Cao Shuangming, showed great interest in MIG-29 fighters. At 
the end of last week, the Chinese representatives could see 
Russian MIG and SU-27 fighters and SU-25 assault planes in the 
Kubinka air field not far from Moscow. 
  Upon his return from Sochi on June 8, the Chinese military 
official is planning to visit the Sukhoi design bureau, the 
Gagarin military aviation academy and the military aviation 
school in Volgograd. A visit to St.Petersburg is also on the 
program of his 10-day visit. 
  Cao Shuangming arrived in Moscow on June 2 on the invitation 
of the Russian air force command. 

</TEXT>

