<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Sitnikov] </F>
  [Text] UN, 7 Jun--A Russian serviceman who is a member of 
the UN Protection Forces has been seriously wounded in Sarajevo. 
This was reported here on Monday by Fred Ekhard, official 
representative of the UN secretary general. 
  "The Russian soldier was seriously wounded by sniper fire in 
Sarajevo on Sunday. Thus, the total number of casualties among 
the staff of the UN Protection Forces is 1,014 wounded and 90 
killed. Only a small part of these casualties have been caused 
by the Bosnian Serbs," Ekhard noted. 

