<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev, Mikhailidhis on Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev, Mikhailidhis on Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606160394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1500 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0606160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev said that 
his country is coordinating its efforts with the Cyprus 
Government on possible new approaches in finding a solution to 
the Cyprus problem. Speaking after a meeting in Moscow with 
Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis, Kozyrev also said that the 
Russian Government wants a solution to be found for the Cyprus 
problem as soon as possible, based on UN decisions on the 
safeguarding of the Cyprus Republic's territorial integrity and 
unity. Kozyrev added that he has discussed with Mikhailidhis 
the possibility of new approaches to the Cyprus issue. In just 
a few words, he said, we coordinated our watches on how we 
should continue working on the issue by keeping in mind that 
Russia is a permanent member of the UN Security Council. 
  Foreign Minister Mikhailidhis said that the discussion he 
had 
with Kozyrev centered on the next steps that will follow on the 
Cyprus issue, after the UN secretary general's report to the 
Security Council. 
  Mikhailidhis continued his contacts and this afternoon met 
with the Russian Parliament President Ivan Rybkin. Later today, 
he will be received by Patriarch Aleksey. 

</TEXT>

