<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paris Club Agrees To Defer Debt Repayments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paris Club Agrees To Defer Debt Repayments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406114794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0958 
GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0406114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikita Yermakov] </F>
  [Text] Paris, 4 Jun -- An agreement on deferring seven 
billion dollars of Russia's foreign debt repayments this year 
was reached here today with representatives of the Paris Club 
which unites 19 creditor states. 
  Russia's total foreign debt, inherited from the former 
Soviet 
Union, is approximately 80 billion dollars. Forty-five billion 
of this is owed to states belonging to the Paris Club. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

