<F P=102>   PM0306151994 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 3 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0306151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Leonid Pozdeyev report: "Americans Buy Rockets in the </F>
Urals"] 
  [Text] Following an exhibition of Russian technologies in 
the United States, the U.S. firm Douglas has concluded a 
contract with Yekaterinburg's "Novator" design bureau. The 
Urals firm has pledged to ship 2,000 rockets to the United 
States. 
  These rockets are not going to join the U.S. Army's arsenal 
but will indirectly help enhance its combat might. The thing is 
that specialists from Douglas intend to use the Russian rockets 
as targets when testing new arms. 

</TEXT>

