<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kondratyev Seeks Peacekeeping Force for Georgia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kondratyev Seeks Peacekeeping Force for Georgia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606114194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1022 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia's Deputy Defense Minister Colonel General 
Georgiy Kondratyev believes that the situation in the zone of 
the Georgian- Abkhazian conflict is explosive. "Although 
large-scale combat operations are hardly possible, armed clashes 
between various groupings may destabilize the situation," he 
told Interfax on Monday. 
  Kondratyev favors the earliest possible despatch of 
peacekeeping forces to this zone. He said, however, that the 
final decision is to be taken by the Russian president, who 
chairs the Council of the CIS Heads of State. 
  To quote Kondratyev, a peacekeeping operation might 
facilitate the return of refugees and a comprehensive settlement 
of the conflict. He also announced that the Russian 
peacekeeping contingent was ready to begin the operation three 
to five days after the decision was taken. 
  A total of 1,500 Russian peacekeepers, consisting of two 
divisions based in the Leningrad and Volga military districts, 
are expected to be sent to the conflict zone. Subsequently, 
peacekeepers from other CIS countries are to join the operation. 

</TEXT>

