<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soskovets Receives Visiting Kazakh Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soskovets Receives Visiting Kazakh Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306161194 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0306161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Kanat Saudabayev, who is on a visit 
to Moscow, met Oleg Soskovets, first deputy chairman of the 
Russian Government. They had a detailed and frank exchange of 
opinions on a wide range of problems of mutual interest. 
Special attention was focused on the necessity to increase 
integration processes both in political and economic spheres. 
Soskovets, in particular, stressed the importance of removing 
the tendency to politization of economy, which has manifested 
itself of late. The sides expressed their belief that it is 
urgent to invigorate work and implement the agreements reached 
during Nazarbayev's first ever official visit to Russia in late 
March. Big hopes to this effect are placed on the 
Kazakh-Russian intergovernmental commission. Concurrently, in 
the interests of overcoming the decline of production, both 
states should actively use possibilities connected with 
development of direct contacts between separate regions and 
enterprises, and encourage targeted investment in business. 

</TEXT>

