<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kazkakh Foreign Minister on Integration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kazkakh Foreign Minister on Integration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306174594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1603 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There are no problems in Russian-Kazakh relations 
which could hamper their integration, Kazakh Foreign Minister 
Kanat Saudabayev said in an interview with Interfax. Saudabayev 
is now in Moscow on a non-official visit. 
  For instance, he said that there were no problems concerning 
the Russian-speaking population in Kazakhstan since this 
amounted to 95 pct of the Kazakh population. 
  Saudabayev stressed that there was no alternative to the 
process of economic, political and cultural integration between 
Russia and Kazakhstan. 
  Today Saudabayev discussed increased cooperation between the 
two countries with Deputy Chairman of the Federation Council 
Ramazan Abdulatipov. Saudabayev announced that they had agreed 
that the legal basis for the integration had already been 
established or was being established. The goal now is to make 
it concrete. 

</TEXT>

