<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Seimas [word indistinct] has presented the 
government with a statement of no confidence against the cabinet 
led by Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius. The statement was 
initiated earlier by the Social Democrats. After receiving an 
official reply, required within 14 days by the government, the 
parliament has five more days to open Seimas discussions. More 
than 50 percent of the parliamentary votes are needed to pass a 
vote of no confidence against the cabinet. 

