<F P=102>   LD0606163494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1521 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] North Korea rejects pressure as a tool to solve the 
nuclear problem of the peninsula. Its Foreign Minister Kim 
Yong-nam said so in Ukraine where he arrived on 6 June. 
  He said that direct talks with Seoul were the only way to 
have the problem solved and that North Korea wanted to make the 
Korean peninsula a nuclear-free zone. 
  Kim Yong-nam expressed the hope that the third round of 
talks 
between Pyongyang and Seoul would bring about positive results 
in that field. 
  He welcomed Ukraine's desire to become a nonnuclear country. 
  Kim Yong-nam and his Ukrainian counterpart Anatoliy Zlenko 
will have talks Monday afternoon. 

</TEXT>

