<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   CIS Interparliamentary Assembly Calls For Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CIS Interparliamentary Assembly Calls For Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806095494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0918 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806095494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Svetlana Ivanova and Lev </F>
Rumyantsev] 
  [Text] St. Petersburg June 8 TASS -- The session of the 
council of the CIS interparliamentary assembly, currently under 
way here, has called for broader interaction among the 
parliaments of the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS). 
  The session, presided over by assembly chairman Vladimir 
Shumeyko, has called on the parliaments of the CIS nations to 
coordinate the actions of all the constitutional bodies in 
drawing up national legislations, elaborating model legal acts, 
and implementing the treaties and agreements adopted within the 
frameworks of the commonwealth. The council stressed the need 
of promoting exchanges of information, holding consultations on 
fundamental problems linked with the development of the CIS. 
  It is planned to discuss during the fifth plenary meeting of 
the CIS interparliamentary assembly, which will be held from 
October 28- 29, a plan for the assembly's efforts to harmonise 
the legislations of CIS nations relating to the economic, 
social, humanitarian, military and other areas of cooperation 
within the CIS. The document was drawn up by standing 
commissions of the interparliamentary assembly. 

</TEXT>

