first time as its full-fledged member. Another first-comer is 
Tajikistan Parliament Chairman Emomali Rakhmonov. 
  The delegation from the National Assembly of Azerbaijan is 
led by Ali Majlis Chairman Rasul Guliyev, that from Armenia by 
Parliament Chairman Babken Ararktsyan. Belarus is represented 
by Mechyslaw Hryb, and Georgia by Parliament Speaker Vakhtang 
Goguadze. The delegation from Kazakhstan is led by the chairman 
of the Supreme Soviet of the republic, Abish Kekilbayev and that 
from Kyrgyzstan by Chairman of the Supreme Soviet Meditkan 
Sherimkulov. 

