<F P=103> LD0706190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 7 ITAR-TASS -- A meeting of Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin and State Duma Speaker Ivan Rybkin was 
held in Kremlin today to discuss interaction of the president 
and the State Duma in the economy and economic legislation, as 
well as the adoption of the budget, the presidential press 
service reports. 
  The sides also discussed information provision of deputies 
and Duma factions. The president hopes the deputies will abide 
by the law on mass media in this sphere. 
  Bearing in mind numerous foreign trips of State Duma 
delegations and deputies, the president expressed concern over 
the Duma spending and budget. 
  The president and the speaker coordinated a number of 
international issues. 

