<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Budget Should be Used to Solve Social, Economic Ills </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Budget Should be Used to Solve Social, Economic Ills </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706224794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1855 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706224794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 7 TASS -- The Russian Government should 
use the 1994 budget revenue reserves to solve the most acute 
social and economic problems, Chairman of the State Duma 
Committee for Budget, Taxes, Banks and Finances Mikhail Zadornov 
told a news conference here today in view of the Duma's second 
reading of the draft 1994 budget. 
  These problems include financial support to Federation 
subjects, defence spending, fundamental science, education and 
preservation of cultural monuments, said the deputy. In his 
opinion, such distribution of budget means will help to preserve 
the defence, scientific and cultural potential of Russia. 
  The money can be found as the "Russian Government has 
envisaged a number of reserves in the draft budget," he said. 
At the same time, the reserves should not exceed the limits of 
the Duma-approved spending, revenues and the budget deficit. 
  For instance, 1,500,000,000,000 rubles can be received from 
cuts of the domestic debt payment. Another 3,000,000,000,000 
rubles can be taken from the reduced amount of foreign drawings. 
It is also necessary to cut by 15 per cent the spending on 
state management structures, whose size has increased by eight 
times as compared to last year, said Zadornov. 

</TEXT>

