<H3> <TI>   Official Calls for Increased Defense Spending </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Calls for Increased Defense Spending </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706164494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1408 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 7 TASS -- The 1994 Russian defence 
budget should be at least 55,000,000,000,000 rubles instead of 
the 37,000,000,000,000 approved by the State Duma, Chairman of 
the Federation Council Budget and Finances Committee Petr 
Shirshov told a news conference here today. 
  In his words, a closed meeting of the parliament upper 
chamber discussed the draft federal budget approved by the State 
Duma in the first reading and decided to agree with the 
committee proposal on the increased defence spending and changes 
in their structure. 
  Shirshov said that the Russian defence budget is only one 
tenth of the U.S. planned military spending. 

</TEXT>

