<F P=102>   LD0706175594 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, the Kazakh cabinet of ministers held a joint 
session with the union of entrepreneurs and industrialists to 
discuss updating and correcting the government's anticrisis 
economic program. First Deputy Prime Minister Akezhan 
Kazhegeldin gave a report on the issue. A new mechanism for 
management of the economy based on making the [word indistinct] 
system healthier and improving mass privatization and investment 
policy was welcomed by the participants. They commented on the 
report sharing their views on ways to boost reform and make 
half-way proposals. They focussed on what is impeding the speed 
of the reforms. The result of an open and interesting 
discussion on possible ways to bring the economy out of the 
crisis was summed up by Prime Mininster Tereshchenko. He said 
that all valuable advice expressed by the participants would be 
taken into account during the further elaboration of the 
anti-crisis program. The head of the government answered 
numerous questions. President Nazarbayev participated in the 
work of the session. 

