<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Successful 3d Investment Privatization Auction Held </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Successful 3d Investment Privatization Auction Held </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806091794 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0806091794 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] The third investment privatization auction was 
held by the Kazakh State Property Committee on 7 June. 
Forty-eight enterprises were to be privatized. Representatives 
of 113 investment privatization funds participated in the 
auction. The minimum rate of stocks was 10 tenge for two 
coupons at the start of the auction, and by its end the rate 
increased by a factor of 3.5 and equaled 6.84 coupons. About 80 
funds managed to buy at least one share. Eighty-four percent of 
stocks were sold as a result of the auction; 33 enterprises were 
completely sold out; one enterprise was not popular at all and 
nobody claimed its stocks. The organizers think this auction has 
been the largest and most successful. 

</TEXT>

