<H3> <TI>   More Than 1,200 Refugees Expected To Return 8 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Than 1,200 Refugees Expected To Return 8 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706164594 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 1200 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tajik </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A new checkpoint was established in the Maksim 
Gorkiy settlement of collective farms named after 1 May -- 
Pyandzhskiy Rayon. 
  Our compatriots can return to their permanent places of 
residence from the Konduz Province of the Islamic State of 
Afghanistan via this checkpoint. This is the fourth checkpoint 
though which our compatriots can return to Tajikistan. Ismat 
Davlatov, deputy Minister of Labor and Employment, told us that 
it was expected that our compatriots will return tomorrow via 
the Hayraton-Termez- Shaartuz highway. It is expected that more 
than 1,200 inhabitants of our republic, who are living 
temporarily in the Islamic State of Afghanistan, will return 
home by train. 

</TEXT>

