<H3> <TI>   Delegation Returns From Talks in Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation Returns From Talks in Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706134694 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 1200 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tajik </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] We are satisfied with our working visit to 
Turkey. The visit was fruitful and promotes beneficial economic 
cooperation between the two states. This was said by Rahimjon 
Ghafurov, first deputy chairman of the Council of Ministers of 
the Republic of Tajikistan, to a correspondent of the KHOVAR 
news agency. 
  Rahimjon Ghafurov was at the head of the country's 
delegation 
that recently visited Turkey. Foreign Economic Relations 
Minister Izatullo Hayoyev, Finance Minister Normat Yunusov; 
Sobit Nematulloyev, president of the republican Academy of 
Sciences; Izatullo Lalbekov, head of the Foreign Economic Bank, 
and others were among the members of the delegation. 
  The Tajik delegation was received by Suleyman Demirel, 
president of the Republic of Turkey. A useful, constructive 
conversation took place on issues related to further developing 
economic relations and to Turkey rendering technical assistance 
to Tajikistan. [passage omitted] 

