<H3> <TI>   Russian Troops Reportedly Enter Abkhaz Territory </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Troops Reportedly Enter Abkhaz Territory </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706185394 Yerevan SNARK in English 1236 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0706185394 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, June 7 (SNARK)--The Russian peace-keeping 
troops are entering the zone of Georgian-Abkhazian conflict, 
said to SNARK the Chairman of the Extraordinary Situations' 
Committee Jaba Ioseliani. 
  In Jaba Ioseliani's words, the process will take 10 days. 
Then two more weeks and the refugees are planned to bring back 
to the Gali region of Abkhazia. The special staffs will do with 
the people's return to their places of living, the staffs will 
work in Sukhumi, Zugdidi and Gali. 

</TEXT>

