<H3> <TI>   Churkin Views Visit Positively, Leaves Tallinn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Churkin Views Visit Positively, Leaves Tallinn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806102394 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1000 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0806102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin said 
at a news conference, which he gave before departing from 
Tallinn today, that he is very pleased with the present 
atmosphere of talks and that goodwill on the Estonian side was 
much in evidence. In addition to talks with Raul Malk, the 
Estonian Foreign Ministry's deputy chancellor, Churkin had a 
meeting yesterday [7 June] with President Lennart Meri and 
Foreign Minister Juri Luik. 
  Churkin opined that both parties genuinely wish to resolve 
all the problems as quickly as possible in order to close a 
chapter in Estonian-Russian relations and open a new one. 
Taking into account the agreements reached in the course of 
Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev's visit to Tallinn at 
the end of May, Churkin thought that talks are nearing the 
finishing line. 
  The next meeting between Churkin and Malk will evidently 
take 
place next week in Moscow. 

</TEXT>

