  [Excerpts] Foreign Minister Juri Luik left for Istanbul 
today where a session of the North Atlantic Cooperation Council 
will take place on 9 and 10 June. [passage omitted] 
  Juri Luik will be making a speech at the session. The 
foreign minister is accompanied by Ambassador Clyde Kull, who is 
the Estonian representative at the cooperation council; 
Ambassador Vaino Reinart, the head of the number one office at 
the Foreign Ministry's policy department; and (Aivo Orav), an 
employee of the office. [passage omitted] 
  Foreign Minister Luik will travel from Istanbul on to 
Beijing, where he will be accompanying President Meri on his 
state visit to China. 

