<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Arms Deal Go-Between Sponsored Election Campaigns </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Arms Deal Go-Between Sponsored Election Campaigns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0806104394 Tallinn ETA in English 1528 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0806104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Go-between in controversial $60 million arms deal 
between Estonia and TAAS Israel Industries Ltd., Leonid 
Apananski, had in 1992 sponsored the election campaign of three 
prominent members of the ruling Fatherland Party, former Defence 
Minister Indrek Kannik told the Estonian Radio on Tuesday. 
Kannik said Apananski had sponsored present Foreign Minister 
Juri Luik, MP Mart Nutt and himself with 9,000 kroons ($692). 
  "I am sorry that those documents from Fatherlandos 
election-time archive should have come out now," Kannik said 
while adding that the archives had stayed with Tiit Pruuli, the 
former adviser to Prime Minister Mart Laar. Kannik also said 
Laar and Pruuli had advised them to ask Apananski for campaign 
funds. Kannik's interview came a day after MP Aivar Kala had 
accused Kannik of accepting Apananski's funds. 

</TEXT>

