<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Freezes Commercial Bank Mandatory Deposits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank Freezes Commercial Bank Mandatory Deposits </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706143394 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1100 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lithuanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The right to use mandatory deposits by the Ateitis 
and Nida commercial banks was suspended yesterday by the 
Lithuanian Central Bank. This was reported by Egle Valyte, 
press spokesman for the Lithuanian Central Bank. 
  The statement disseminated by the Lithuanian Central Bank 
today stresses that this decision is aimed at protecting the 
interests of the creditors. The decision was made after the 
Lithuanian Central Bank administration made amendments to the 
rules on mandatory reserves of commercial banks on 3 June. The 
use of mandatory reserves deposited at the Lithuanian Central 
Bank are restricted if the banks violate their obligations and 
are not able to settle accounts in full with their creditors. 
  We have already reported that the Apus, Express, and 
Lietukis 
commercial banks had their right to use the mandatory reserves 
suspended by the Administration Board of the Lithuanian Central 
Bank on 3d June. 

</TEXT>

