<H3> <TI>   Moscow Negotiations on 14th Army Withdrawal Resume </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Negotiations on 14th Army Withdrawal Resume </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706171894 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1945 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0706171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 6/6/1994 -- The 9th round of 
Russian-Moldovan negotiations on the status and terms of 14th 
Army's withdrawal will begin tomorrow in Moscow. BASA learned 
from the Defense Ministry Press Secretariat that Nicolae 
Turtureanu, head of the military experts' group of the Moldovan 
delegation, will not take part in the negotiations due to an 
illness. According to some sources from the Defense Ministry, a 
new head of the military experts' group has not been appointed 
yet. Moldovan delegation is headed by Nicolae Osmochescu, prime 
vice minister of foreign affairs. A Dniester delegation is 
taking part in the negotiations. A representative of the 
Moldovan Government stated to BASA that Tiraspol representatives 
by no means can be regarded as a third side in the negotiations. 
"According to an agreement between the Moldovan and Russian 
delegations, Tiraspol was allowed only to be present at the 
negotiations without a right to make statements," said the 
quoted source. 

</TEXT>

