<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Car Bomb Kills 1, Wounds Logovaz Director </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Car Bomb Kills 1, Wounds Logovaz Director </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706184294 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1700 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Several hours ago, a terrorist act was perpetrated 
in Moscow. Our correspondent D. Matyushin has just returned 
from the location. 
  [Matyushin] There was a powerful explosion this afternoon at 
about 0500 hours, near Paveletskiy railway station, alongside 
the famous Logovaz company. Eyewitnesses stated that as Logovaz 
General Director Boris Berezovskiy was driving his car out of 
the gates, a nearby car stuffed with explosives blew up. The 
driver was killed and the director general's bodyguard was badly 
wounded. Boris Berezovskiy himself received burns to his face. 
He was in a state of shock and was taken to the hospital. A 
driver who was passing by at the time of the explosion was also 
hurt. The exploded empty car had Lithuanian license plates and 
a remote control device had been placed in it. According to 
Yuriy Kolpakov, head of the department of city procuracy, it was 
a planned attempt on the life of the director of Logovaz. 
  In Moscow alone in the past six months there have been 10 
such assassination attempts. [Video shows badly damaged car, 
people milling around street] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-39395 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov110_b_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-110 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

