<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Seeks Ban on Democratic Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Seeks Ban on Democratic Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806120894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1125 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806120894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 8 TASS -- The Liberal Democratic Party 
of Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, whose programme and tactics were often 
compared to that of Adolf Hitler, fired back on Wednesday 
branding the "Democratic Russia" movement as "fascist" and 
demanding to ban it. 
  Vyacheslav Marychev, a member of Zhirinovskiy's faction in 
the State Duma, proposed to discuss the issue of "banning the 
anti-popular fascist movement `Democratic Russia'" because, 
according to him, it is to blame for the current economic plight 
of the country. 
  The "Democratic Russia" was the major movement which helped 
Boris Yeltsin come to power. 
  The Duma rejected the proposal and Speaker Ivan Rybkin 
stressed that such a question is outside the powers of the lower 
chamber. 

</TEXT>

