<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parties Holds Anti-Zionist Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parties Holds Anti-Zionist Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK0706115094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 7 Jun 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK0706115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report in the "Non-Stop Around the Clock" </F>
column: "Rutskoy Faces a Poor Outlook in Israel"] 
  [Text] Recently a theoretical conference was organized at 
the Central Travelers House entitled "The Ideology of State 
Patriotism and the Struggle Against International Zionism." 
  The conference was initiated by the State Party [Derzhavnaya 
Partiya] led by Terekhov, the Communist Party of Russia, the 
Officers Union, and the Public Committee for Legality and 
People's Power. Apart from politicians, the `struggle' class 
was attended by AL-QUDS publisher Sha'ban, who rented the 
Central Travelers House. Various points of view were aired at 
the meeting but Dr. Sha'ban left everybody else behind. He 
stated that he had personally recruited Russian guys to send to 
Israel on a reconnaissance mission. And now he has 
incontestable evidence that in the south of Israel there are 
secret bases with chemical and bacteriological weapons. 
Allegedly, tests on humans are also conducted there. Another 
speaker explained to the audience that Rutskoy's mother is 
Jewish. In Israel, therefore, he would never be elected even to 
a lousy municipality, let alone the vice presidency. 
  Officers Union leader Stanislav Terekhov explained to 
MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS's correspondent that the aim of the 
conference is to work out a political course and an ideological 
program for the State Party. Terekhov does not intend to 
affiliate with Rutskoy's State [Derzhava] political movement. 
His decision is final and irrevocable. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

