<H3> <TI>   Latest on Privatization, Chubays-Luzhkov Controversy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Latest on Privatization, Chubays-Luzhkov Controversy </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Filatov Supports Chubays </H4>

<F P=102> LD0706221994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1445 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706221994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 7 TASS -- "Law is on Chubays' side". 
Sergey Filatov, chief of the Russian president's administration, 
said this in answer to a question from ITAR-TASS about his stand 
on a conflict regarding privatisation between Russian Deputy 
Premier, Chief of the State Committee on Property Anatoliy 
Chubays and Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov. 
  Filatov believes that to change the rules of privatisation 
of 
state property 20 day before the validity of vouchers expires 
means to undermine the confidence of citizens in the authorities. 

</TEXT>

