<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Latest on Privatization, Chubays-Luzhkov Controversy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Latest on Privatization, Chubays-Luzhkov Controversy </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Luzhkov Allows Registration of Joint Stock Companies </H4>

<F P=102> LD0706222294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1639 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706222294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By BUSINESS-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 7 TASS -- Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov has 
canceled his instruction of April 1, 1994, which banned 
registration of joint stock societies in Moscow, the press 
service of the Russian State Committee for Property reports 
today. 
  Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin sent a letter to 
Luzhkov on May 27 to demand cancellation of the illegal 
instruction within three days. The mayor told a news conference 
on June 3 he does not plan to change his instructions and "will 
gladly go to the procurator's office" to prove the correctness 
and lawfulness of "special privatization" in the Russian capital. 
  "The cancellation proves that Yuriy Luzhkov has admitted 
gross violations of Russian legislation, presidential decrees 
and government resolutions on privatization. The Federal 
Committee for State Property Management is ready to help Luzhkov 
in restoration of lawful privatization in the city of Moscow," 
says a statement of the press service. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

