<H3> <TI>   Satellite Parameters Given </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Satellite Parameters Given </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706184794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1825 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 7 TASS -- A Cosmos-2281 artificial earth 
satellite was launched on June 7, 1994, by the Soyuz 
rocket-booster from the Russian Plesetsk launching grounds in 
the interests of the Russian Defence Ministry. 
  Sources at the ground mission control center report that the 
satellite has been put on the orbit with the following 
parameters: 
  - the initial period of rotation - 88.7 minutes; 
  - the maximum distance from the earth surface (in the 
apogee) 
- 265 kilometers; 
  - the minimum distance from the earth surface (in the 
perigee) - 192 kilometers; 
  - the inclination of the orbit - 82.6 degrees. 
  The on-board equipment is functioning normally. 

</TEXT>

