<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference on Space Biology Conducted From Orbit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference on Space Biology Conducted From Orbit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706131794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1204 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Marina Barinova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 7 TASS -- Cosmonauts Viktor Afanasyev, 
Yuriy Usachev and Valeriy Polyakov opened on Tuesday an 
international conference on space biology and aerospace medicine 
by a reportage on research now conducted on board the orbital 
station Mir. Doctor Valeriy Polyakov offered to scientists a 
report containing the results of medical research for which he 
was the object. 
  Corresponding member of the Russian Academy of Sciences 
Anatoliy Grigoryev, academician of the Russian Academy of 
Medical Sciences, director of the Institute of Medico-Biological 
Problems, then took the floor. He noted that 430 reports 
reflect all the aspects of the problems discussed. They sum up 
new results received from experiments on biological satellites 
and in prolonged space flights and after the studying the state 
of the organism in extreme circumstances during flights or 
diving. All these reports are of fundamental nature but also 
have practical importance. This data will be used for medical 
ensurance of flights and underwater work, including the 
selection, training medical checks, prophylactics and treatment 
of diseases and rehabilitation. 
  Questions of international medico-biological cooperation in 
space will also be discussed at the meeting attended by 
representatives of many countries, and also representatives of 
the European Space Agency. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

