<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Says Time `Not Yet Ripe' for DPRK Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Says Time `Not Yet Ripe' for DPRK Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706133794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1300 GMT 
7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev believes 
that the time is not yet ripe for international sanctions 
against North Korea. In an interview for INTERFAX before flying 
to Paris, he stressed that sanctions can be introduced in stages 
but only after all other possibilities have been exhausted. In 
the minister's view, the main possibility is an international 
conference. Andrey Kozyrev also noted that international 
measures should be introduced and lifted by the UN Security 
Council alone. 

</TEXT>

