<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Attends Paris OECD Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Attends Paris OECD Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Signs Economic Agreements </H4>

<F P=102> LD0806122094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1123 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Dmitriy Gorokhov, Nikita </F>
Yermakov and Igor Shchogolev] 
  [Text] Paris June 8 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev today signed a package of agreements with the 
Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD). 
It includes a declaration on cooperation between the Russian 
Federation and the OECD and an agreement between the Russian 
Government and the OECD on the organisation's privileges and 
immunities in the Russian Federation. 
  The documents were also signed by OECD Secretary-General 
Jean-Claude Paye and chairman of the OECD council session, 
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister of Ireland Dick Spring. 
  The declaration on cooperation envisages, among other 
things, 
that Russia will now enjoy the status of observer in various 
OECD bodies, that it will get access to information possessed by 
the organisation. The OECD will draw up surveys of the economic 
situation in Russia, will make recommendations for the 
implementation of economic reforms, and will assess their 
effectiveness. The second document signed today lays down the 
terms for the work of OECD experts in Russia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

