<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Attends Paris OECD Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Attends Paris OECD Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hails New Ties </H4>

<F P=102> LD0806132194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1211 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0806132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Dmitriy Gorokhov, Nikita </F>
Yermakov and Igor Shchegolev] 
  [Text] Paris, 8 Jun -- Closer ties with the Organization 
for Economic Cooperation and Development [OECD], an organization 
embracing 25 of the world's most developed countries, will make 
a real contribution to Russia's integration with the world 
economy. This was stated today by Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev in his address at the signing of a declaration on 
cooperation between the Russian Federation and the OECD and an 
agreement between the Russian Government and the OECD on the 
granting of privileges and immunities for the organization 
within the Russian Federation. The ceremony was held today at 
the Paris headquarters of this international organization. 
  These documents "pave the way for the expansion of effective 
cooperation between Russia and the OECD in the long term and the 
mutually complementary interests of both countries," the 
minister said. "Thanks to its material and natural resources, 
Russia's involvement with the OECD will help to further enrich 
trade, economic, scientific, technical, and intellectual 
exchanges in the extensive Euro-Atlantic and Pacific region," 
the minister noted. He feels that these documents also provide 
"further important evidence of the world community's support for 
economic reforms in Russia." 

</TEXT>

