<H3> <TI>   Memorandum of Understanding Signed With OAS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Memorandum of Understanding Signed With OAS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806114194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0653 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0806114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Chistov] </F>
  [Summary] Brasilia, 8 Jun -- Russia has signed a memorandum 
of mutual understanding with the Organization of American States 
(OAS). Russia has been a permanent observer with the OAS since 
1982. The memorandum sets the guidelines for cooperation 
between Russia and the OAS. Russia Deputy Foreign Minister 
Georgiy Mamedov, who signed the memorandum on Russia's behalf, 
also delivered to the OAS general secretary, Juao Clemente Baena 
Soares, a message from the Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev. 

</TEXT>

