<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Cancels Economic Limits on Abkhazia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Cancels Economic Limits on Abkhazia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706164194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1405 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Boris Krivoshey] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 7 TASS -- Russia canceled economic 
limits on Abkhazia on May 24, 1994, bearing in mind positive 
changes in the Sukhumi stand on Georgian-Abkhazian settlement 
and the grave economic position of the Abkhazian side resulting 
from the armed conflict, head of the Russian Foreign Ministry's 
Information and Press Department Grigoriy Karasin told a 
briefing here today. 
  "Certainly, corresponding issues should be settled with due 
account of our essential stand on recognition of territorial 
integrity of the Georgian republic," said Karasin. 
  In his words, the United Nations Security Council's 
secretariat held consultations on cooperation in peace-keeping 
in Abkhazia late in May in New York. The consultations were 
held in the presence of Russia. 
  "Their main result is the end to watchfulness as regards the 
Commonwealth plans of a peace-keeping operation in Abkhazia, and 
understanding of the need for close interaction between our 
peace- makers and the U.N. mission in the conflict zone," said 
the Russian Foreign Ministry's representative. 

</TEXT>

