<H3> <TI>   Turkey to Provide $35 Million To Gagauzia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkey to Provide $35 Million To Gagauzia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706205394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1613 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkey will allot a 35 million dollar-credit for 
development of Gagauzia. President of the self-proclaimed 
Gagauz Republic Stepan Topal told Interfax in an interview on 
the results of the visit of Turkish President Suleyman Demirel 
that 32 million would be utilized for supply of the region with 
drinking water and 3 million would go for development of the 
infrastructure. 
  Topal hoped that the problem concerning the political status 
of the southern Moldovan region mostly populated by Gagauz, 
would be resolved in the near future. He suggested that this 
would help to stabilize the social-political situation in the 
region and to attract foreing investments. 
  Commenting on relations with the Transdniestrian leadership, 
Topal said they remained the same and were proceeding from the 
treaty on friendship and cooperation signed in 1992. 
  The fact that Gagauzia seeks cooperation with Turkey rather 
than with Transdniestria cannot hinder our relations. "Together 
with Transdnietsria we have stood for preservation of the USSR 
and we will not refuse from cooperation with the ex-Soviet 
republics, primarily with Russia," Topal pointed out. 

</TEXT>

