<F P=103> LD0706160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Boris Krivoshey] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 7 TASS -- A Russian state delegation 
headed by Ambassador at Large Yuriy Dubinin will fly to Kiev on 
Wednesday to continue the negotiations on the Black Sea Fleet. 
  The delegation includes Supreme Commander of the Russian 
Navy 
Admiral Feliks Gromov, Russian Deputy Minister for Cooperation 
with Member-Countries of the CIS, German Kuznetsov, and other 
officials. Grigoriy Karasin, spokesman for the Russian Foreign 
Ministry told this a briefing on Tuesday. 
  "The main purpose of the Russian delegation is to try to 
ensure that questions standing on the road to working out an 
agreement on the initial stage of the settlement of the problem 
of the Black Sea Fleet are resolved at the meeting in Kiev on a 
basis of principles and directives worked out and coordinated at 
the summit level", the spokesman said. 

