<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz June 7 TASS -- "The Caucasus should be 
viewed as a single whole, local processes influence the 
public-political situation in the Russian south," Russian 
Minister for Nationalities and Regional Policy Nikolay Yegorov 
told a meeting here today. 
  The meeting was attended by North Ossetian President 
Akhsarbek Galazov, North Ossetian Government and Presidium 
members, head of temporary administration Vladimir Lozovoy and 
representatives of federal ministries currently in the state of 
emergency zone to discuss the implementation of presidential 
decrees and governmental instructions on the return of refugees 
and forced migrants to places of their permanent residence. 
  In the opinion of Yegorov, developments in the conflict zone 
influence the whole North-Caucasian region, and the refugee 
problem should be solved with due account of this situation. He 
stressed that the North Ossetian-Ingush relations should be 
settled only peacefully and without the use of force. 
  Yegorov, Lozovoy and members of the North Ossetian 
Government 
visited the state of emergency zone this morning to meet local 
residents. 
  The minister has left Vladikavkaz. 

</TEXT>

