<H3> <TI>   Vladivostok Mounts Major Anti-Crime Effort </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vladivostok Mounts Major Anti-Crime Effort </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944F0777B Vladivostok VLADIVOSTOK in Russian 4 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> 944F0777B </F>
<F P=104>  Vladivostok VLADIVOSTOK </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Report by Sergey Filonenko: "Vladivostok Becomes a </F>
Battlefield"] 
  [Text] Large-scale operations to combat organized 
crime will commence in Vladivostok in the first days of 
June. 
  This was stated at a news conference last Friday by Vladimir 
Ipatov, chief of the kray's Internal Affairs Administration. 
Additional forces of the militia will be pulled in from other 
cities and rayons of the kray. It is planned in the very near 
future to organize inspections of the gang "haunts" and secret 
addresses and the motor transport and papers of all suspects, 
which will last for several months. 
  So concentrated an assault on the city's crime is connected 
with the events that occurred at the end of last week and the 
start of this, when several militia officers were killed and 
wounded. In retaliation, 145 persons were detained and eight 
guns and seven radios were confiscated in literally a matter of 
days. The militia officers arrested 45 persons at a gathering of 
crime groupings, at which narcotics, weapons, $55,000, and 
approximately R50 million were confiscated. 

</TEXT>

