<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko, </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 7 June TASS -- Ukraine has a reliable partner 
in the person of North Korea on the international scene, North 
Korean Foreign Minister Kim Yong-nam told First Deputy Ukrainian 
Parliament Speaker Oleksandr Tkachenko here today. 
  In his words, North Korea fully supports Ukraine in its 
building of independent democratic state and expresses the 
assurance it will take a worthy place in the international 
community. The North Korean foreign minister praised the 
Ukrainian decision to become a non-nuclear state. 
  He highly estimated the foreign policy of Ukraine which 
stands for the solution of all problems at negotiations and on 
the basis of international norms and thanked the Ukrainian side 
for support to peaceful unification of North and South Koreas. 
  In his turn, Tkachenko estimated the visit of the North 
Korean delegation is "the deepening of friendship and legal 
basis for the development of further mutually beneficial 
cooperation." He thanked the foreign minister for the 
invitation to visit North Korea and said "the date of this visit 
will be coordinated in the near future." 

</TEXT>

