<H3> <TI>   Says Army Should Stay `Aloof' From Politics </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says Army Should Stay `Aloof' From Politics </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706194494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1807 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian Army should stay aloof from politics, 
according to Ukrainian President and Supreme Commander of Armed 
Forces Leonid Kravchuk. "Political feuds should not touch the 
Army," he told a conference of chief executives devoted to army 
issues in Kiev today. 
  "According to the requirements of the times, the armed 
forces 
and the state machinery must be permanently ready to defend 
Ukraine, its sovereignty and territorial integrity," Kravchuk 
said. He pointed out that the Army's main goal was to maintain 
the country's ability to defend itself and maintain the 
inviolability of its borders. 
  The Ukrainian Defense Ministry press service told 
INTERFAX-Ukraine that the conference had been attended by the 
leaders of government, Defense Ministry and the military complex. 
  The conference touched on a wide range of issues embraced by 
the single goal to achieve a qualitative change in the 
management of the Ukrainian armed forces. 

</TEXT>

