<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Government Commission To Examine Budget Deficit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Government Commission To Examine Budget Deficit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806093194 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0845 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- As a UNIAN correspondent learned from 
confidential sources on 7 June, a special budgetary commission 
has been created in Ukraine's Cabinet of Ministers, which 
includes ministers and deputy ministers of the economy, 
statistics, and finance, and also the chairman of the board of 
the National Bank of Ukraine. Acting Prime Minister Yukhym 
Zvyahilskyy will confirm a draft of the commission's work. 
  The commission is to examine the deficit of the new budget 
until the end of the year (this budget is now being elaborated 
by the Ministry of Finance), discuss the possibility of reducing 
the expenditure part of the budget, and to submit proposals on 
reducing the budget deficit in accordance with IMF demands, 
which are also being adjusted. 
  As Viktor Yushchenko, the chairman of the National Bank of 
Ukraine said, as of today, the Ministry of Finance's debt to the 
state is 50 trillion karbovantsi and if the Ministry of 
Finance's debts are not confirmed in the new budget there could 
be an inflationary explosion in Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

