<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oil Production Down 15 Percent in Last 5 Months </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Production Down 15 Percent in Last 5 Months </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806090694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0836 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By BUSINESS-TASS for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 8 TASS -- The production of oil with gas 
condensate in Russia during the first five months of 1994 has 
come to 124.4 million tonnes, a drop of 15.2 percent in 
comparison with the same period of 1993, Ministry of Fuel and 
Energy told BUSINESS- TASS. 
  The largest quantity of oil -- 77.6 million tonnes -- was 
extracted by the state enterprise "Rosnephth" during 
January-May, 1994. The oil company "Lukoil" produced 17.5 
million tonnes, the "Surgutnephtegaz" 14.4 million tonnes and 
the "Yukos" 11.3 million tonnes. 
  The gas production came to 266.5 billion cubic metres, a 
fall 
of 2.1 percent. The "Gazprom" extracted 250.6 billion cubic 
metres of gas, and oil industry enterprises a total of 12.8 
billion cubic metres. 
  The production of coal during this period was 117.6 million 
tonnes, a drop of 10.5 percent. 
  Oil supplies to former Soviet republics accounted for 36.8 
million tonnes, a rise of 10.5 percent. Gas exports came to 
44.8 billion cubic metres, increasing by 3.6 percent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

