<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kiev To Back UN Sanctions Against DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kiev To Back UN Sanctions Against DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706174794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1613 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine will support the UN decision on sanctions 
against North Korea due to its refusal to allow IAEA experts to 
its nuclear sites. If the decision is taken, we shall support 
it, the Ukrainian Foreign Ministry spokesman Yuriy Sergeyev told 
a briefing in Kiev Tuesday [7 June]. 
  He said that as a UN member, Ukraine is obliged to implement 
and is implementing all decisions of this international 
organization. He cited Ukraine's position concerning UN 
sanctions against Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

