<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on CIS Interparliamentary Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on CIS Interparliamentary Session </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Shumeyko Briefs Media </H4>

<F P=102> LD0906003494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1534 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906003494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Summary] St. Petersburg, 8 Jun--At a news conference 
following the conclusion of the session of the CIS 
Interparliamentary Assembly Council here, Council Chairman 
Vladimir Shumeyko said that it had drafted practical measures 
for implementing its resolution: "On The Role of the 
Interparliamentary Assembly of the CIS Member States and Its 
Tasks in Further Strengthening the CIS." 
  A decision was also made to call on the CIS parliaments to 
speed up the ratification of multilateral agreements concluded 
within the CIS and to call on the Council of CIS heads of state 
to take coordinated action to harmonize legislatures and prepare 
model laws on such issues as refugees and Afghan war veterans. 
  The session also heard a report by Medetkana Sherimkulov, 
head of the interparliamentary group on a peace settlement for 
Nagorno- Karabakh, on the results of the May 1994 Bishkek 
meeting on settling the conflict in Nagorno-Karabakh. 
  A decision was also made to hold the fifth plenary session 
of 
the Interparliamentary Assembly on 28-29 October 1994 in St. 
Petersburg, as well as an international conference on perfecting 
criminal law on the territory of the CIS. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

