<H3> <TI>   Reportage on CIS Interparliamentary Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on CIS Interparliamentary Session </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Civil Code `Model' on Agenda </H4>

<F P=102> LD0806123594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1202 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg June 8 TASS -- In line with a 
decision taken on Wednesday by the council of the CIS 
interparliementary assembly, the CIS private law research and 
consulting centre will begin to elaborate a model civil code of 
CIS countries. 
  This is expected to lay groundwork to bring the national 
civil legislations of the CIS countries closer together on such 
key economic integration-related matters as the legal status of 
commercial organisations, freedom of goods traffic and 
transactions, the proteciton of foreign investors' interests, 
the development of legislation on contracts and guarantees of 
the discharge of obligations, and the establishment of a similar 
procedure to resolve economic disputes. 
  A model civil code is to be referred for adoption to the CIS 
interparliamentary assembly session in October. 

</TEXT>

