<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on CIS Interparliamentary Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on CIS Interparliamentary Session </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Admiral Urges Peacekeeping Forces </H4>

<F P=102> LD0806121994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1138 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg June 8 TASS -- Vladimir Shumeyko, 
chairman of the council of the CIS interparliamentary assembly, 
and Admiral Aleksandr Mochaikin, representative from the 
headquarters for coordinating CIS military cooperation, 
recommended the participants of the session of the 
interparliamentary assembly's council, currently under way in 
St. Petersburg, to set up CIS peace- keeping forces. 
  Interviewed by ITAR-TASS, the admiral stressed the urgent 
need to set up such units. There are only Russian disengagement 
forces were on the territory of the CIS at present, but their 
status does not correspond to the U.N. mandate on peace-keeping 
forces. According to Mochaikin's forecast, not all the CIS 
nations will be ready to assign their troops for peacekeeping 
missions, but their contribution, he believes, could be 
financial or in the form of equipment deliveries. 
  In case today's appeal to the MPs to set up CIS 
peace-keeping 
forces is met, the question will have to be discussed at the 
level of the CIS council of defence ministers and council of 
foreign ministers so that corresponding proposals could be 
submitted to the next plenary meeting of the interparliamentary 
assembly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

