<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former Candidate Said To Join Opposition Presidential Team </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former Candidate Said To Join Opposition Presidential Team </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0906085994 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1445 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0906085994 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to People's Deputy Syarhey Navumchyk, who 
is also the coordinator of the Belarusian Popular Front 
parliamentary opposition, Henadz Karpenka, a former contender 
for the presidential post, has agreed to join Zyanon Paznyak's 
presidential team. It is not ruled out, Navumchyk stated, that 
in the event of Paznyak's victory in the presidential elections 
Henadz Karpenka will be appointed prime minister. 
  The joining of Paznyak's team by this politician, in 
Navumchyk's opinion, is helpful in three ways: First, such a 
political personality would do credit to any democratic 
organization; this will also be helpful to the state in general. 
Second, this is an important step in unifying democratic forces 
in Belarus. Finally, Karpenka has good connections in Russia's 
political circles, which is also of great importance. 

</TEXT>

