<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester Defense Minister Opposes 14th Army Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dniester Defense Minister Opposes 14th Army Withdrawal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0806143994 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2000 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0806143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 7/6/1994 -- "Moldovan 
leadership's decision not to insist on the 14th Army's 
withdrawal in the summer of 1994 during the ninth round of 
negotiations is without doubt a positive fact," told BASA 
Stanislav Khazheyev, defense minister of the self-proclaimed 
Dniester Republic. General Khazheyev mentioned that it is unreal 
for the withdrawal to take place by 1 July 1994. He said that 
several years are needed for the 14th Army's withdrawal. He 
also pointed out that Dniester representatives who take part in 
the negotiations will have the possibility to make public their 
position on this matter. Khazheyev said that he is confused 
that the Dniester representatives took part in the negotiations 
only as observers. "The Dniester Republic should take part in 
the talks with full rights," he said. Khazheyev pointed out 
that the Tiraspol Supreme Soviet's decision to pass the 14th 
Army's property to Dniester will not be annulled. 

</TEXT>

