<H3> <TI>   Official Reiterates Autonomy Plans for Gagauzia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Reiterates Autonomy Plans for Gagauzia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0806142994 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2000 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0806142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 7/6/1994 -- "After Turkish 
President Suleyman Demirel's visit to Moldova, the draft law on 
spectral juridical status for the districts densely inhabited by 
Gagauzians has not been changed," stated to BASA Victor 
Greben-scicov, presidential counselor. According to him, the 
Turkish president gave no directives to the Comrat leaders in 
this regard. "The Comrat leaders had previously received several 
foreign delegations at a quite high level which, in my opinion, 
were useful for all sides," added Grebenscicov. He noted that 
the Turkish president insisted on preservation of Moldova's 
integrity. "I do not share the opinion of those who say that 
the law on status for the districts densely inhabited by 
Gagauzians would lead to Moldova's federalization," specified 
Grebenscicov. He pointed out that the draft law supposes 
decentralization. "This implies a broad autonomy and not a 
republic," he said. 

</TEXT>

