<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Addresses Parliament on Economic Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev Addresses Parliament on Economic Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906050594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0442 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906050594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Akimov] </F>
  [Text] Almaty 9 June TASS--A regular plenary session of the 
parliament of Kazakhstan began here on Thursday [9 June] with a 
speech by President Nursultan Nazarbayev. 
  Prior to the session, the president had addressed the 
parliament in a message, advocating an acceleration of 
market-oriented reforms and suggesting a wide package of 
measures to take the country's economy out of the crisis. 
  The message was officially referred to the parliament 
secretariat on Thursday morning. In the afternoon the message 
is expected to be presented to the deputies for study and 
discussion. 
  According to competent sources, the message makes a 
political 
evaluation of the internal situation in the country and 
Kazakhstan's foreign-policy stand, and the reform process, and 
analyses the activities of state power bodies to implement the 
strategic policy of building a democratic state with a market 
economy. 
  At the same time the message defines key orientations of 
state policy consistently to carry out reforms in all spheres of 
economic and social life, strengthen Kazakhstan's statehood and 
the socio-political unity of the peoples inhabiting it. 
  The message formulates clearly political and economic goals 
and sets appropriate tasks to power and administration bodies 
for a subsequent period. 
  The presidential message is manifestly aimed at 
consolidating 
all branches of state power and all forces of society and at 
mustering the efforts of all political parties, movements and 
associations and all robust potential of the state with a view 
to taking the country out of the deep crisis, deepening reforms, 
contributing towards democracy and strengthening the Republic's 
sovereignty. 

</TEXT>

