<H3> <TI>   Grachev Arrives; Karabakh Issue on Agenda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev Arrives; Karabakh Issue on Agenda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806165694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1646 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Lyloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan June 8 -- Russian Defense Minister Pavel 
Grachev arrived today in the Armenian capital. "It is a 
scheduled visit connected with a summer training season that has 
started in Russian troops deployed in Armenia," the minister 
told ITAR-TASS Upon his arrival. 
  According to Grachev, during his visit the question of 
Russia's military bases on the Armenian territory should be 
settled together with that of the deployment of Russian 
peace-keepers in the Karabakh conflict area. 
  Grachev told TASS that, although his visit to Azerbaijan was 
not scheduled, he will go there at the request of Azeri 
President Gaydar Aliyev. Russian President Boris Yeltsin has 
okayed his several hour stopover in Baku, the minister added. 
  Grachev said that he will insist that the agreements drafted 
by defense chiefs of Russia, Armenia, Azerbaijan and 
Nagorno-Karabakh "should be signed by all means." "No one will 
decide for us," the minister stressed. 

</TEXT>

