<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Moscow Ostankino Television First 
Channel Network in Russian at 1700 GMT on 8 Jun, in the 
"Novosti" newscast, carries a report on Russian Defense Minister 
Pavel Grachev's arrival in Armenia. Speaking on his latest 
proposal on the introduction of Russian peacemaking forces in 
the Azeri-Nagorno-Karabakh conflict zone, Grachev makes the 
following comment: 
  "The agreement--which I consider a good one--should 
definitely be signed if the sides want peace. On 11 June I will 
go from Georgia to Azerbaijan for a few hours. I will plainly 
tell Azeri President Geydar Aliyev that I support the agreement 
signed in Moscow. I will tell him that if Azerbaijan does not 
agree to it I will simply walk away from this issue." 

</TEXT>

