<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan June 9 TASS -- Russian Defence Minister 
Pavel Grachev, who arrived in Armenia on Wednesday, is visiting 
today the Russian troops deployed in the republic. Grachev is 
familiarising himself with the course of military training, 
supplies to the troops and their daily life. 
  The Russian minister told ITAR-TASS that he intended to meet 
officers, sergeants and soldiers to discuss priorities. 
  On Wednesday, Grachev and Armenian President Levon 
Ter-Petrosyan discussed the deployment of Russian military bases 
in Armenia. According to an agreement signed by the two 
countries' leaders, a Russian motor-rifle division has been 
deployed in Giumri and a regiment has been based near Yerevan. 
  Grachev was satisfied with the level of cooperation with the 
Armenian Defence Ministry. He called the interaction between 
the Armenian national army and the Russian troops deployed in 
Armenia "the best possible". 
  The Russian minister is scheduled to meet the leadership of 
the Armenian Defence Ministry later today. 

</TEXT>

