<H3> <TI>   Parliament Accepts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Accepts </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Foreign   Investments Law 

<F P=102> NC0806204994 Yerevan SNARK in English 1630 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0806204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, June 8 (SNARK)--Today Armenian Parliament 
accepted the Foreign Investments Law. 
  Speaking to the Parliament of Armenia Tigran Sargisyan, 
chairman of the finance and budget commission, said that the 
foreign investors are supplied not only with the same modes as 
the citizens of the republic but also with the certain 
privileges to stimulate the in-flow of the foreign capital. "We 
can't achieve certain success in privatization and other spheres 
without foreign investments", said Tigran Sargisyan. 
  According to the law, the foreign investors can 100 per cent 
own the enterprises distributed on the territory of Armenia. 
Meanwhile, they have the right to acquire securities and create 
joint ventures in Armenia. 
  Foreign investments in Armenia are out of the 
nationalization. 

</TEXT>

