<H3> <TI>   Welcomes Peacekeepers' Deployment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Welcomes Peacekeepers' Deployment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0806203994 Yerevan SNARK in English 1620 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0806203994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, June 8 (SNARK)--The peace-keeping forces' 
deployment in the zone of the Georgia-Abkhazian conflict will be 
not only a guarantee of stability but also will promote building 
of the Georgian Army. Vardiko Nadibaidze, Georgian Defence 
Minister, declared of it at a press-conference in Tbilisi. He 
also reported that the peace-keeping forces will be composed of 
3 battalions from the Urals, St. Petersburg and Siberian 
military districts. 
  The united headquarters of the peace-keeping forces will be 
placed in Sukhumi and the local ones in Gali and Zugdidi. The 
security zone, where the refuges' return is planned, will 
stretch till the town of Ochamchira. Mentioning the special 
role of Russia in the cause of Georgian Army building, the 
Minister said the later should be united, scanty-10-15 thousand 
people and mobile". Nadibaidze also said he hoped Russian 
Defence Minister Pavel Grachev would arrive in Georgia after 
finishing his visit to Armenia. 

</TEXT>

