<H3> <TI>   Einseln Says Defense Forces Could Expel Russians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Einseln Says Defense Forces Could Expel Russians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0806134194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 8 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0806134194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Igor Golin report under "KRASNAYA ZVEZDA and Agency </F>
Correspondents Report" rubric: "Estonian Military Flexing Its 
Muscles?"] 
  [Text] Tallinn -- The following BNS (BALTIC NEWS SERVICE) 
report has been circulated in Baltic countries' mass media: 
Estonian Defense Forces Commander Alexander Einseln has stated 
that the Estonian Defense Forces can easily cope with the 
Russian military grouping stationed in Estonia and, if 
necessary, can expel the "Russian militarists" by force. 
  "We are ready to to this if we are given such an order," 
Einseln stated. The agency points out that currently there are 
approximately 2,500 Russian servicemen in Estonia, the deadline 
for whose withdrawal has still not been agreed, while the 
Estonian Defense Forces have between 5,000 and 6,000 soldiers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

