<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Kulbitskiy] </F>
  [Text] Mainz June 9 TASS -- All reports in the Russian 
press about possible changes in the leadership of the Russian 
Government, including allegations concerning Viktor 
Chernomyrdin's possible resignation as prime minister, are 
"absolutely at variance with reality and no more than 
inventions", according to sources close to the head of the 
Russian Government, who is now undergoing medical examination 
and treatment in the urological clinic of Johann Gutenberg 
University. 
  The sources said the medical consultations, which followed 
the preliminary medical examination in connection with the prime 
minister's nephrolithiasis, proceeded successfully. According 
to the same sources, some forces were obviously seeking to bank 
on the current situation. 

