<F P=106> [Nikita Gololobov report in the "Power" column: </F>
"Chernomyrdin Will Soon Return to Moscow. German Specialists 
Say His Health Is Excellent"] 
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] According to the DPA agency, 
"seven specialists have examined Chernomyrdin but made no 
diagnosis. According to chief urologist Professor Rudolf 
Gogenfellner, Chernomyrdin's health condition is excellent." 
  The question arises: Is Chernomyrdin's unexpected trip to 
Germany a way of "setting the stage" for his resignation "for 
health reasons"? It is noteworthy that, according to a source 
in the Russian Foreign Affairs Ministry, people from the 
entourage of First Vice Premier Oleg Soskovets, who are 
currently staying with him in Malaysia, indicated that their 
"chief" might soon become prime minister. Oleg Soskovets, who 
did not rule out such a possibility, seems to be further 
distancing himself from his boss. 
  Another likely candidate for the post of head of government 
-- Commodity Producers Federation Chairman Yuriy Skokov -- is 
behaving amazingly calmly in this situation. According to a 
source in the federation apparatus, the federation is working in 
a normal mode. 

