<H3> <TI>   Gaydar Says Yeltsin Backs Russia's Choice </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gaydar Says Yeltsin Backs Russia's Choice </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK0906082794 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 8 Jun 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK0906082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report in the "Non-Stop Around the Clock" </F>
column: "Gaydar Has Breached an `Iron Curtain'"] 
  [Text] The day before yesterday Boris Yeltsin and Yegor 
Gaydar had an eye-to-eye meeting. MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS asked 
Yegor Timurovich for details. The Russia's Choice leader said 
that they had discussed the general political situation in the 
country and problems related to the package of economic edicts 
both already signed by the president and those that will come 
out shortly. During their confidential meeting they also 
discussed the formation of the Russia's Choice party, in which 
the president is taking an "interest." Chances are that Yeltsin 
will not attend the Choice founding congress on 12 June but, 
according to Gaydar, he relates positively to Russia's Choice, 
and the formula "Russia's Choice is the party the president 
leans on" is still in force. 
  Just a few months ago democratic leaders were complaining 
about the Yeltsin apparatus, which "closed" the president to 
contacts. Now, however, Yegor Timurovich noted, "the situation 
is developing in an extremely positive way." 

</TEXT>

