<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says Russia Faces Economic Catastrophe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says Russia Faces Economic Catastrophe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806150394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1416 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806150394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 8 TASS -- Russian communist leader 
Gennadiy Zyuganov described the economic situation in Russia as 
catastrophic. 
  Speaking at a news conference in Moscow on Wednesday, 
Zyuganov said that the country has become completely 
ungovernable and social tension continues to grow. Social and 
economic ties are falling apart. 
  Summing the results of his trip to several Russian regions, 
Zyuganov said that local officials called for a strong and 
capable government whose powers must be separated from the 
powers of presidential structures, which, as they claim, 
"interfere in the economic management" and get in the 
government's way. 
  To solve the food problem, Zyuganov suggested "establishing 
the minimum consumer basket and returning to state regulation of 
prices of basic necessities, including rationing." 
  He stressed the need for changing the liberal economic 
policy 
which has failed. "We will have to use measures of state 
regulation, primarily in power engineering, transportation, 
communications and agriculture," he said. 
  Zyuganov also believes that Russia should offer Ukraine, 
Byelorussia [Belarus] and Kazakhstan to set up a body to 
coordinate economic management and restore the severed ties. 
Another task is to fight crime and corruption and restore law 
and order in the country. 
  Zyuganov noted that no one will support the idea of a 
general 
political strike in Russia, adding that the question of early 
presidential elections -- in September-October -- "may emerge 
within the presidential structures themselves." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

